editorialSummary.text: Fashionable American leather-goods brand known for its signature handbags, plus shoes & accessories.

originalText.text:
I came to purchase my Coachtopia bag a few months ago and it was a great experience! All the salespeople were very friendly and helpful with sizing.

I returned today to add a flower “charm” to my bag and it was a wonderful time seeing all the color choices and placements. Thank you Bruno for being so thoughtful and knowledgeable with the flower placement and compositions. He gave some really great suggestions that I ended up going with, and wasn’t pushy about anything, and the end result brought a big smile to my face! I definitely love my bag even more now with the customizations. Thank you Prince st Coach!!

originalText.text: We went to visit this store during the Coachtopia pop-up. The employees were super kind and helpful, and we left with some gorgeous new purses!

originalText.text:
Beyond my expectation! I stopped by months ago and store was closed during lockdown. Today I just shop around SOHO and decide to check this store again. I hear about new stuff is coming in March - April but I just want to know maybe they have some new items early.

It is a small store but the service is so friendly and professional. I talk to Jackie and another SA and they all helpful and knowledgeable. I ask about some items that won't be in US but they will be in another legions and one of the SA be able to tell me all of the questions I ask. I give them my number and they can text me when item I want is available.

I definitely revisit this store again.

originalText.text: By the time I got to Coach I was many stores in trying to find the perfect purse. I was on a mission and staff sensed it , and didn’t bombard me or push anything on my I wasn’t interested in. When I found the perfect bag they all hyped me up. Jason was amazing, he made me feel like a person rather than a potential sale. It was such a refreshing experience!

originalText.text: The sales attitude is very good, but I am very dissatisfied with the security guard at the door. When I was holding my daughter with one hand and pushing the stroller with the other, the security guard saw it and didn't even want to open the door for me. Just watching my 6-year-old daughter pull the heavy glass door open. When we finish shopping and go out, we still open the door ourselves. I know it's not necessary to open the door. But when I saw a mother with two children in such a store, she refused to help open the door. Really disappointing shopping experience!
